Root cause: $effect read $page.params.id which subscribes to the whole $page store (Svelte 4 store, not fine-grained). history.replaceState inside load() triggers SvelteKit's store sync, emitting a new $page object, re-triggering the effect. The SSE rename (message→agent_message) in the previous commit was a red herring — valid practice but not the cause. Fix: $derived extracts just the ID string so the effect depends on a primitive, not the store object. Also guarded ?msg= with a flag and used window.location instead of $page.url.
